Package de.iabg.mode

Interface Summary
MaterialReader This interface declares basic functionality for parsing a file containing material data, namely mass and stiffness matrices.
ModeConnectionWriter This interface declares basic functionality for writing a file containing mode connection data.
ModeCorrelationModel This interface declares basic functionality for correlating two mode shape matrices.
ModeCorrelationUI This interface declares basic functionality for the user interface of a JModeCorrelationPanel.
ModeCorrelationWriter This interface declares basic functionality for writing a file containing mode correlation data.
ModeModel This interface declares basic functionality for storing data for a dynamic mode shape matrix.
ModeReader This interface declares basic functionality for parsing a file containing mode shape data.
ModeUI This interface declares basic functionality for the user interface of a JModePanel.
 

Class Summary
DefaultModeModel This implementation of ModeModel attempts to create all the functionality described in the ModeModel class description.
JModeCorrelationFrame A JFrame for a standard JModeCorrelationTabbedPane.
JModeCorrelationPanel An implementation for for correlating two mode shape matrices.
JModeCorrelationTabbedPane This JTabbedPane assembles all the necessary JPanel components to create a fully integrated mode correlation component.
JModeMirrorPanel An implementation for a JPanel containing two JModePanel objects with the First Mode panel placed vertically above the Last Model panel.
JModePanel An implementation for storing data for a dynamic mode shape matrix.
MassMatrix This Matrix is designed to store the influence values of a given mass matrix.
MassMatrixMap This ComboBoxModel is backed by a LinkedHashMap since there are several instances where it is convenient to have this combination.
ModalAssuranceCriterionModel This implementation of ModeCorrelationModel attempts to create all the functionality described in the ModeCorrelationModel class description.
ModeConnectionMatrix This Matrix is designed to store a connection or mapping between two objects of ModeMatrix.
ModeCorrelationMatrix This Matrix is designed to store the values of a correlation between all modes of two objects of ModeMatrix.
ModeCorrelationScene2D This class creates a content scene graph for the visualization of a 2D matrix in Java3D.
ModeCorrelationScene3D This class creates a content scene graph for the visualization of a 3D matrix in Java3D.
ModeCorrelationTableModel This implementation of a TableModel provides a table representation of a ModeCorrelationMatrix.
ModeMatrix This Matrix is designed to store the mode shape coordinates of a given mode shape matrix.
ModeTableModel This implementation of a TableModel provides a table representation of a ModeMatrix.
OrthogonalityCheckModel This implementation of ModeCorrelationModel attempts to create all the functionality described in the ModeCorrelationModel class description.
